The first major development lay in the presidency\'92s reach beyond oversight. Trump\'92s own words did much of the work. Early in the week he labeled a video by six Democratic veteran lawmakers \'93seditious behavior\'94 and called for their arrest and trial, even hinting that such conduct was \'93punishable by death.\'94 The video itself simply reminded service members of their duty to refuse unlawful orders. By framing that reminder as treason, the president signaled that legal fidelity, when it cut against his wishes, would be treated as a crime. This was not a stray outburst. It fit a broader pattern in which opposition was tolerated on paper but chilled in practice, and in which the language of sedition and treason was pulled into ordinary partisan dispute. The chill was the point.\
